bid.t.sol
├─ given the contract is paused
│  └─ it should revert
└─ given the contract is not paused
   ├─ when the function is reentered
   │  └─ it should revert
   └─ when the function is not reentered
      ├─ when the auction has not started
      │  └─ it should revert
      └─ when the auction has started
         ├─ when the auction has ended
         │  └─ it should revert
         └─ when the auction is live
            ├─ when the computed amount of auctioned asset is zero
            │  └─ it should revert
            └─ when the computed amount of auctioned asset is greater than zero
               ├─ it should transfer the auction asset to the receiver
               ├─ when callback data is provided
               │  ├─ when the callback to the receiver fails with return data
               │  │  └─ it should revert and bubble up the receiver error message
               │  └─ when the callback to the receiver fails without return data
               │     └─ it should revert
               ├─ it should transfer the asset out from the receiver to the Auction contract
               ├─ it should emit an AuctionBidSettled event
               └─ when there are no more asset to auction
                  └─ it should emit an AuctionSettled event
